<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFD60CE81CCA0" blockId="44.[227,679,718,746]" box="[227,679,718,746]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FF7AFD60CD5BCCA2" bold="true" box="[227,381,718,745]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD2E5A07FF7AFD60CD06CCA3" box="[227,288,719,745]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
(by original designation)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFD52C843CD17" blockId="44.[226,1436,765,861]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FF7AFD52CE61CD5D" authority="Michelotti, 1847" authorityName="Michelotti" authorityYear="1847" box="[227,583,765,791]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elatus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FF7AFD52CD5CCD5D" box="[227,378,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Conus elatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FE18FD52CE61CD5D" author="Michelotti G." box="[385,583,765,791]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref31024" refString="Michelotti G. 1847. Description des fossiles des terrains miocenes de l'Italie septentrionale. A. Arnz &amp; Comp." type="book" year="1847">Michelotti, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Burdigalian of 
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD2E5A07FC98FD52CF11CD5D" box="[769,823,765,791]" name="Italy" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Italy</collectingCountry>
(Colli Torinesi) (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FB99FD52C85CCD52" author="Hall C. A. Jr." box="[1024,1146,765,792]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="111 - 171" refId="ref29646" refString="Hall C. A. Jr. 1966. Middle Miocene Conus (Class Gastropoda) from Piedmont, Northern Italy. Bollettino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana 3 (2): 111 - 171." type="journal article" year="1966">Hall 1966</bibRefCitation>
); Langhian of Paratethys (see 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FE81FCB0CE7DCD73" author="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B." box="[280,603,799,826]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref29682" refString="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B. 2016. A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 1 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau 2016</bibRefCitation>
for more references); Tortonian of 
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD2E5A07FC6CFCB0C80DCD73" box="[1013,1067,799,825]" name="Italy" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Italy</collectingCountry>
(Sant’Agatha fossili, Stazzano, Montegibbio) (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FE0AFCEDCE0DCD16" author="Sacco F." box="[403,555,834,860]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref31718" refString="Sacco F. 1893 a. I molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonte e della Liguria. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Torino." type="book" year="1893">Sacco 1893a</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD2E5A07FDF5FCEDCE99CD16" box="[620,703,834,860]" name="Greece" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Greece</collectingCountry>
(Messara Basin, 
<collectingRegion id="A445F878DD2E5A07FC12FCEDCFEACD16" box="[907,972,834,860]" country="Greece" name="Kriti" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Crete</collectingRegion>
) (this work).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD2E5A07FF7AFC2CCDA8CA7E" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFC2CCD7ACDD7" blockId="44.[227,348,899,925]" box="[227,348,899,925]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD2E5A07FF7AFC2CCD7ACDD7" bold="true" box="[227,348,899,925]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FF7AFC2CCD7ACDD7" bold="true" box="[227,348,899,925]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFC1ECDA8CA7E" blockId="44.[227,1437,945,1076]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Elongated last whorl, medium to high spire whorl height, beaded early spire whorls. Spiral sculpture on the ramp finely to distinctly striate. Subsutural flexure shallow (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FC6DFC7BC92BCDA4" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." box="[1012,1293,980,1006]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Deep-very deep, moderately-strongly asymmetrical, moderately-strongly curved, subsutural flexures (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FB60FC59CDA4CA7E" author="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref29682" refString="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B. 2016. A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 1 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD2E5A07FF7AFBF5CEC2CB67" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFBF5CD73CA3E" blockId="44.[227,341,1114,1140]" box="[227,341,1114,1140]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD2E5A07FF7AFBF5CD73CA3E" bold="true" box="[227,341,1114,1140]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FF7AFBF5CD73CA3E" bold="true" box="[227,341,1114,1140]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD2E5A07FF7AFB27CEC2CB67" blockId="44.[226,1437,1160,1325]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FF7AFB27CE21CAE8" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." box="[227,519,1160,1186]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio (2009)</bibRefCitation>
first described 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FD21FB27CF6DCAE8" authorityName="Tucker &amp; Tenorio" authorityYear="2009" box="[696,843,1160,1186]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Plagioconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FD21FB27CF6DCAE8" box="[696,843,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Plagioconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at genus level and were followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FB63FB27CDB4CA8C" author="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref29682" refString="Harzhauser M. &amp; Landau B. 2016. A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 1 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, who, in turn, proposed an emended description, according to their Paratethyan species. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FE58FB62CEE1CAAD" author="Puillandre N. &amp; Bouchet P. &amp; Duda T. F. &amp; Kauferstein S. &amp; Kohn A. J. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Meyer C." box="[449,711,1229,1255]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="290 - 303" refId="ref31454" refString="Puillandre N., Bouchet P., Duda T. F., Kauferstein S., Kohn A. J., Olivera B. M., Watkins M. &amp; Meyer C. 2014. Molecular phylogeny and evolution of the cone snails (Gastropoda, Conoidea). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 78: 290 - 303. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.05.023" type="journal article" year="2014">
Puillandre 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FDA6FB61CE5CCAAD" box="[575,634,1229,1255]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
(2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD2E5A07FD4BFB62CF28CAA2" author="Puillandre N. &amp; Duda T. F. &amp; Meyer C. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Bouchet P." box="[722,782,1229,1256]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref31531" refString="Puillandre N., Duda T. F., Meyer C., Olivera B. M. &amp; Bouchet P. 2015. One, four or 100 genera? A new classification of the cone snails. The Journal of Molluscan Studies 81 (1): 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eyu 055" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
) placed many genera of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FBB2FB62C8ABCAAD" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1822" box="[1067,1165,1229,1255]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Conidae</taxonomicName>
as subgenera under the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FEB7FB5FCD5FCB40" authorityName="Eschewegi Pereira da Costa" authorityYear="1866" box="[302,377,1264,1290]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FEB7FB5FCD5FCB40" box="[302,377,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Conus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Morphologically, this group of species can be included in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FB3AFB5FC8C8CB40" authorityName="Eschewegi Pereira da Costa" authorityYear="1866" box="[1187,1262,1264,1290]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FB3AFB5FC8C8CB40" box="[1187,1262,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Conus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus, we refer here to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD2E5A07FEA2FABCCDE8CB67" authorityName="Tucker &amp; Tenorio" authorityYear="2009" box="[315,462,1299,1325]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Plagioconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD2E5A07FEA2FABCCDE8CB67" box="[315,462,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Plagioconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the subgeneric level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
